Privacy Policy

Last updated: May 23, 2024.

Welcome to Globe Defender!

This privacy policy explains how I collect, use, and share information about you when you use my mobile application Globe Defender (the "App").

1. Information I Collect

Personally Identifiable Information (PII):

I do not collect any personally identifiable information directly through my App.

Non-Personally Identifiable Information:

Usage data such as gameplay statistics, session length, and in-game actions.

2. Data Transmission
The App may transmit non-personally identifiable information such as usage data to my servers to improve the game experience and for analytics purposes.

3. How I Use Your Data
To improve game functionality and user experience.
To analyze usage patterns to enhance our services.
To fix bugs and ensure the security of the App.

4. Data Deletion Requests
You can request the deletion of your data by contacting me at huibergs.games@gmail.com. I will respond to your request within a reasonable timeframe.

5. App Permissions
The App requires the following permissions:

To store your Google Play name: This permission is needed to save your results to leaderboards.

6. Contact Me
If you have any questions or concerns about this privacy policy, or if you need to report a security vulnerability, please contact me at: huibergs.games@gmail.com

7. Changes to This Privacy Policy
I may update the Privacy Policy from time to time and will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page. You are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes. Changes to this Privacy Policy are effective when they are posted on this page.

By using the App, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy.


